    public class OneToOneDoublePartioner
extends AbstractDoublePartitioner
    Partitions the data to ensure that only one value will be in a group by itself. Even though this not an effective algorithm it can be used to benchmark other algos

    • Method Detail

      • partition

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,java.util.List<java.lang.Double>> partition(java.util.List<java.lang.Double> values,
                                                                                   java.lang.Double maxSum)
        Takes a list of values and divides them into groups. The resulting groups are such that the sum of the values in the subset are less than a provided maxSum.
        Parameters:
        values - a list of doubles that need to be partitioned
        maxSum - each group must not exceed this sum when the individual values are added
        Returns:
        A list that contains many groupings of values that are less than the provided maxSum
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentExpection - if the maxSum is less than or equal to zero
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if values contain a null value
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if maxPartitionSize is null
